subject: http://zelos.ai/knowledge/ProfileAthlete/1355250
object: In 2017 he suffered from a collarbone injury that ruled him out of the 2017 Spanish Championships in Valladolid. He also sustained a broken thumb that year. (gimnasialatina.com, 11 Jul 2017; plazadeportiva.valenciaplaza.com, 23 Feb 2018)In early 2011 he tore the anterior cruciate ligament [ACL] in his right knee while practising a floor exercise. He was unable to compete for a year and missed the qualifying tournaments for the 2012 Olympic Games in London. In 2014 he tore his ACL again while competing at a World Cup event in Cottbus, Germany. He underwent surgery in April 2014 and returned to competition a year later.

subject: http://zelos.ai/knowledge/ProfileAthlete/1355250
object: He has received the Juan Agudo Garat  as the Athlete of the Year in Alcoy, Spain, in 2013, 2015, 2016, 2018 and 2019. (diarioinformacion.com, 15 Nov 2018, 14 Nov 2019)He was named 2016 Male Athlete of the Year in the Alicante province in Spain.

subject: http://zelos.ai/knowledge/ProfileAthlete/1355250
object: He began gymnastics at age four at Club Gimnastico Pastoret in Alcoy, Spain.

subject: http://zelos.ai/knowledge/ProfileAthlete/1355250
object: He used to go with his parents to watch his sister training and he asked to join the gym too. "I think that what hooked me the most was how this sport allows me to move my body. The movement is limitless."

subject: http://zelos.ai/knowledge/ProfileAthlete/1355250

subject: http://zelos.ai/knowledge/ProfileAthlete/1321381
object: He began rowing at age 14 at the Circolo Nautico Stabia rowing club in Italy.

subject: http://zelos.ai/knowledge/ProfileAthlete/1321381
object: He was involved in swimming and basketball before his physical education teacher encouraged him to take up rowing. "I quickly found good friends. I got in the boat and understood what it means to have healthy and fair competition. In basketball the mothers of opponents were shouting at me about everything. I think that is highly counterproductive and certainly does not allow young people to become passionate about a sport."

object: He began playing handball at age 14 at secondary school in Ivry-sur-Seine, France. He was introduced to the sport by a friend who was already playing.

subject: http://zelos.ai/knowledge/ProfileAthlete/1350409
